headline: Will Starbucks' AI tools, menu items be enough to up store traffic?
summary: Foot traffic at coffee chain Starbucks (SBUX) has exhibited flattening growth as the frequency of customer visits is still down from pre-pandemic levels. Placer.ai head of analytical research R.J. Hottovy joins Market Domination to break down what employee artificial intelligence (AI) tools and new protein drink menu offerings mean for store traffic, according to his firm's latest data. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.
